tournament.name: Regional Championship - Ultimate Guard European Magic Series

decks.notes: This deck focuses on using Underworld Breach in combination with fast mana sources like Mox Opal and Mishra's Bauble to generate a lot of mana and loop through spells and artifacts from the graveyard to achieve a game-winning combo. Cards like Grinding Station and Emry, Lurker of the Loch play a key role in this strategy, while Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student helps with card selection and searching for combo pieces. The deck aims to quickly assemble the combo pieces and win the game by either milling the opponent out with Thassa's Oracle or dealing lethal damage with Malevolent Rumble.

The deck focuses on utilizing mana ramping cards to quickly cast powerful Eldrazi creatures and control the board with spells like Kozilek's Return and Malevolent Rumble. It also includes cards like Karn, the Great Creator to further disrupt opponents' strategies. The deck aims to overwhelm opponents with massive threats like Emrakul, the Promised End and World Breaker, while maintaining control through a combination of removal spells and disruptive abilities. With a mix of ramp, control, and powerful threats, the deck aims to dominate the game and outvalue opponents in longer matchups.

The main focus of this Boros Aggro deck is to quickly overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures such as Guide of Souls, Ocelot Pride, and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, supported by powerful spells like Galvanic Discharge and Fable of the Mirror-Breaker. The deck also includes cards like Static Prison and Thraben Charm to control the board and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The mana base is optimized for consistency, with fetch lands like Arid Mesa and Marsh Flats, and utility lands like Arena of Glory and Elegant Parlor. Overall, the strategy revolves around applying pressure early and maintaining it throughout the game.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on using aggressive creatures such as Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, supported by powerful planeswalkers like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah. The deck also utilizes burn spells like Galvanic Discharge and Goblin Bombardment to control the board and pave the way for quick victories. Static Prison and Chained to the Rocks help to disrupt the opponent's strategy, while Fable of the Mirror-Breaker provides additional card advantage. The mana base is carefully constructed to ensure consistent access to all necessary colors of mana.

This deck focuses on assembling a fast and powerful combo using Underworld Breach and Grinding Station to create a loop that mills the opponent's deck and eventually wins the game with Thassa's Oracle. Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student provide card advantage and help set up the combo. The deck is built around efficient artifact mana and can recur key pieces from the graveyard multiple times. Overall, the strategy is to quickly and efficiently execute the combo while disrupting the opponent's game plan.

The deck focuses on assembling the Broodscale Bloodchief combo utilizing cards like Glaring Fleshraker and Basking Broodscale to generate value and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck runs a number of utility cards like Walking Ballista, Ancient Stirrings, and Urza's Saga to help find key pieces of the combo and control the board. Emrakul, the Promised End acts as a game-ending threat, while cards like Kozilek's Command and Malevolent Rumble provide disruption and removal. The mana base includes lands like Eldrazi Temple and Cavern of Souls to support the Eldrazi creatures in the deck.

The deck focuses on aggressive creatures like Psychic Frog and Territorial Kavu to deal damage quickly. It also includes powerful spells like Tribal Flames and Lightning Bolt for additional damage. The inclusion of Leyline of the Guildpact and Leyline Binding helps to control the board while cards like Stubborn Denial and Spell Snare provide protection. The mana base is diverse with fetch lands and triomes to ensure consistent color access. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with efficient creatures and burn spells to secure a fast victory.

This deck focuses on ramping up mana quickly to bring out powerful Eldrazi creatures and control the game through various spells and abilities. By utilizing cards like Utopia Sprawl and Talismans, the deck can accelerate its mana production and cast devastating spells like Emrakul, the Promised End and Kozilek's Return. Karn, the Great Creator provides additional utility by shutting down opponent's artifacts, while cards like Sowing Mycospawn and Devourer of Destiny help to control the board and overwhelm the opponent with unstoppable Eldrazi creatures.

The main concept of this Modern 1 vs 1 deck is to utilize the synergy between Amulet of Vigor, Primeval Titan, and various land cards to generate powerful combos and ramp up mana quickly. By utilizing cards like Bojuka Bog, Urza's Saga, and Green Sun's Zenith, the deck aims to control the board and build towards a win condition, such as using Scapeshift to search for Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle and deal massive damage to the opponent. The deck focuses on efficient land plays and strategic decision-making to overwhelm the opponent with powerful Titan combinations.

The deck focuses on assembling a variety of creatures that can be searched for and brought into play through various tutoring and ramp spells. Combining smaller creatures like Cauldron Familiar and Gilded Goose with larger threats like Samwise Gamgee and Amalia Benavides Aguirre allows for a versatile and flexible gameplay style. The deck also utilizes cards like Chord of Calling and Green Sun's Zenith to search for specific creatures when needed. Ultimately, the goal of the deck is to create a toolbox of creatures that can adapt to any situation and overwhelm the opponent.

The main concept of this deck is to maintain control over the board by utilizing a combination of aggressive creatures and disruptive spells. By utilizing cards like Fatal Push and Solitude to remove threats and Aether Vial to cheat creatures into play, the deck aims to pressure opponents while disrupting their game plan. The deck also includes creatures like Ephemerate and Flickerwisp to provide additional utility and value. Overall, the strategy revolves around efficient removal, disruptive plays, and aggressive creatures to outmaneuver opponents and secure victory.

The deck focuses on disrupting opponents while steadily building up your own board presence through efficient creatures and disruptive spells. By utilizing cards like Aether Vial and Recruiter of the Guard to quickly get your key creatures onto the battlefield, you can quickly overwhelm your opponent with a mix of aggression and disruption. Cards like Fatal Push and Skyclave Apparition help to disrupt your opponent's game plan while your aggressive creatures like Overlord of the Balemurk and Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd quickly close out the game. Overall, the deck aims to control the tempo of the game and secure a quick victory.

This Jund Aggro deck focuses on disrupting and removing opponent's threats while applying pressure with efficient and aggressive creatures. It utilizes a combination of discard spells like Thoughtseize and Inquisition of Kozilek, removal like Fatal Push and Unholy Heat, and powerful threats like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Tarmogoyf. The deck also includes versatile cards like Nihil Spellbomb and Wrenn and Six for card advantage and utility. The land base is optimized to support the aggressive game plan and maximize the deck's potential.

The main focus of this deck is to disrupt the opponent's game plan while applying pressure with aggressive creatures. By utilizing cards like Aether Vial and Ephemerate, the deck can quickly get ahead on board presence and keep the opponent on the back foot. Cards like Flickerwisp and Skyclave Apparition can deal with troublesome threats, while Emperor of Bones and Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd provide a strong offensive presence. The deck also incorporates elements of resource denial with cards like Recruiter of the Guard and Witch Enchanter, making it difficult for opponents to execute their strategies effectively.

This deck focuses on controlling the board while utilizing powerful Elemental creatures and spells to maintain dominance. By using a combination of removal spells, card draw, and versatile creatures like Risen Reef and Omnath, Locus of Creation, the deck aims to outvalue opponents and overwhelm them with a steady stream of threats. The inclusion of Six','','');">Wrenn and Six helps to recur key lands and provide card advantage, while Leyline Binding helps to lock down opposing threats. Overall, the deck aims to establish control early and maintain it throughout the game.

The main concept of this deck revolves around utilizing cascade spells to cheat out powerful creatures like Curator of Mysteries and Windcaller Aven. By cycling through cards such as Street Wraith and Generous Ent, the deck can quickly build up a board presence and disrupt the opponent's strategy with cards like Subtlety and Endurance. Living End serves as the primary combo piece, allowing the player to return all creatures from their graveyard to the battlefield. With the support of cards like Force of Negation and Teferi, Time Raveler, the deck aims to control the board while setting up for a game-winning Living End.
